archimate:DataObject.name: WANProtocol
archimate:DataObject.documentation: WAN Protocols operate at the lowest three levels of the OSI model (i.e.; physical; data link; and network) and are used to define communications over different types of wide-area media. The SID model defines ATM; FrameRelay; HDLC; ISDN; PPP; SLIP; SMDS; and X.25 as examples of subclasses of this class.
